=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: React 3-bromobenzenesulfonyl chloride with 3-pyridylmethylamine in the presence of base (e.g. Et3N/pyridine, CH2Cl2, 0 °C to rt) to form the sulfonamide intermediate Brc1cccc(S(=O)(=O)NCc2cccnc2)c1. | Step 2: Subject this aryl bromide sulfonamide to Heck coupling with methyl acrylate (Pd(OAc)2/PPh3 or Pd(dppp)Cl2, amine base, DMF, heat) to install the styryl ester and give COC(=O)C=Cc1cccc(S(=O)(=O)NCc2cccnc2)c1 (predominantly E). | Step 3: Convert the methyl ester to the hydroxamic acid by hydroxaminolysis with NH2OH·HCl plus base (e.g. NaOMe, K2CO3, or Et3N in MeOH/THF) to furnish the exact target O=C(C=Cc1cccc(S(=O)(=O)NCc2cccnc2)c1)NO.

